2. cs.RO - The paper deals with solving a scheduling problem, which is a common problem in Robotics (RO) and Operations Research (OR). 
3. cs.LG - The paper uses machine learning techniques such as RL to improve the performance of the HH framework, which falls under the subfield of Machine Learning (ML). 
4. cs.DS - The paper deals with solving a large, highly constrained timetabling problem, which involves data structures (DS) and algorithms. 
5. cs.SE - The paper deals with solving a real-world problem in the domain of software engineering (SE), which involves scheduling exams for students.
